directed to the midplane from the\nsurface regions. The mass accretion mainly occurs near the surfaces and the gas\nnear the midplane slowly moves outward, which causes large-scale meridional\ncirculations. The vertical magnetic fields are also dragged inward in the\nsurface regions, while they stochastically move outward and inward around the\nmidplane. We also discuss an observational implication of induced spiral\nstructure in the simulated turbulent disks to protoplanetary disks.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 26 Sep 2013 14:26:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 9 Dec 2013 11:47:37 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 18 Dec 2013 11:47:15 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 17 Jan 2014 13:04:04 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Mon, 20 Jan 2014 07:56:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-17"}
